after we initiate project we should tell git to track our files
we can use
"git add ." or "git add all"
to move all files on stage so git will track these files from now

Note: when git start track a file, he get track it always
      (it will be exist on stage area)
      so we just need introduce it just once (like when we use "add ." at first time)
      so if we create "new file" we should add it to stage manually
      then git will track it automatically.


Note: we can add multiple files by space:
      git add file1 file2 file3

      we can add all multiple files by patterns:
      git add .txt (add all text files)

      we can add all files recursively:
      git add .    (be carful, sometimes we have some files we don't want to
                    add to git)


Note: we can use
      "get staus"
      to what we have on STAGE
      we can see if we have some files that we don't track them!
      we can see if we have some files on stage that need to be commit


example: we have been used git on design pattern 1 until now,
         we delete exercise folder on section 8,
         we add these changes to stage area by:
         "git add ."
         now are stage is ready he just need to be commit to move
         these changes to our repository (local repository)